    "top_event": "Loss of Containment - Trapped Pressure Release",
    "incident_type": "Uncontrolled pressure release with equipment ejection",
    "costs": "4000",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Safety stand down called",
      "Onsite investigation initiated",
      "BSEE inspection conducted February 3, 2023",
      "Contractor to install slip-on surface wellhead on all wells with subsea wellhead systems",
      "Contractor to update standard operating procedures to include pressure control equipment before perforating untested annuli"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 31, 2023, during temporary abandonment operations of the E-4 well at Ship Shoal 224 E platform, an electric line casing cutter was fired at 120 feet below mud line. Trapped pressure in the annulus between the 10-3/4 inch and 7-5/8 inch casing was released when the casing was cut below the subsea wellhead tieback system. The pressure release ejected the tool string from the well, damaging grating on the cellar and wellbay decks. No injuries occurred. The crew was unaware that the well did not communicate above or below the subsea tieback system, and no wireline pressure control equipment was used because the surface wellhead had been removed in 2007.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Install slip-on surface wellhead on all wells with subsea wellhead systems",
      "Update standard operating procedures to include pressure control equipment before perforating untested annuli"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "trapped pressure",
      "subsea wellhead tieback system",
      "tool string ejected",
      "no communication above or below subsea tieback",
      "no wireline pressure control equipment",
      "electric line casing cutter"
    ]
  },
